{
  "texts": [
    "Semistructured interviews with internal governance teams could reveal challenges in operationalizing systemic risk assessments (Code: RA) across different services [169], allowing evaluation of provisions like standardized reporting flows (Code: DD) in Article 31 and participation in risk analysis (Code: RA) under Article 26.",
    "Focus groups surveying external citizen attitudes pre/post adoption facilitate gauging perceived impacts on information quality and algorithmic transparency (Code: AT) tied to Articles 24 and 29-30.",
    "This provides multi-stakeholder contextualization of shifts attributable to key provisions.",
    "Specific questions could also be directed towards trusted flaggers under Article 15, examining experiences submitting notices (Code: NTD) and interacting with evolving notice-and-takedown platforms.",
    "Polling similarly enables quantifying user perceptions on experiences with online accountability measures [69].Ethnographic Observation Interviews and embedded analysis within digital oversight bodies and technology firms aids directly examining operational adaptations arising from DSA due diligence obligations (Codes: NTD, DD, RA)."
  ]
}